This should be unnecessary, as based on my understanding the code is only invoked at the server side.

{code}
+    } else if (e instanceof UnresolvedLinkException) {
+      s = Response.Status.GONE;
{code}

Should this be 404 instead of 410? In UNIX, opening a unresolved symlink return {{ENOENT}}.

[~daryn], I think putting calling {{getFileStatus}} in open to get FNF, and keep the old lazy open will have the same effect.

